# openRS_ Release Checklist

Every time a new app version is released (versionName bump in `build.gradle.kts`), ALL of the following must be completed **before** committing and pushing:

## 1. CHANGELOG.md
- `android/CHANGELOG.md` — add a new `## [vX.Y.Z] — YYYY-MM-DD` section at the top
- Describe every fix and change under clear headings (`### Fixed`, `### Added`, `### Changed`)

## 2. Root README.md (single source of truth)
- **Root** `README.md` version badge: `https://img.shields.io/badge/version-X.Y.Z-blue`
- CAN ID table: reflect any ID additions/removals/corrections
- OBD polling table: reflect any new/removed PIDs or formula changes
- Feature descriptions: update if any features were added or removed
- Do NOT update `android/README.md` with shared content — it links to root

## 3. Browser Emulator

File: `android/browser-emulator/index.html`

This file mirrors the app UI. Every visible change to the app **must** be reflected in the emulator in the same commit/release. Check each category:

- **Version badge** — update `openRS_ vX.Y.Z` text in the `<div class="version-badge">`
- **Data cell labels** — if any `dc-label` text changed in the app (e.g. "FUEL RAIL" → "HP FUEL"), update it in the emulator
- **New widgets / rows** — if a new row was added to any tab (e.g. odometer row, new data cell), add matching HTML in the emulator
- **Removed widgets** — if something was removed from the app (e.g. gear display), remove it from the emulator too
- **MORE tab sections** — if a new section was added (e.g. "Module Status"), add it to the emulator; if a section heading changed, update it
- **Feature cards** — if a Features card was added, renamed, or its locked/unlocked state changed, reflect that in the emulator
- **TPMS decimal places** — `displayTire()` must use `.toFixed(1)` for PSI to match the app
- **Demo data** — simulated values should reflect real-world plausible readings
- **`toggleOdom()` or any new JS toggle** — if a new interactive element was added to the app, add matching JS in the emulator

## 4. Firmware (if firmware also changed)
- `firmware/CHANGELOG.md` or release notes must be written
- Firmware version bumped in `focusrs.h` (`OPENRS_FW_VERSION`)
- `firmware/patches/apply_patches.py` — `OPENRS_FW_VERSION` must match `focusrs.h`
- Compiled binaries must be rebuilt and placed in `firmware/release/`
- A separate `fw-vX.Y` GitHub release must be created with all 4 flash files

## 5. GitHub Release
- Commit, then create and push tag: `git tag android-vX.Y.Z && git push origin android-vX.Y.Z`
- Create release: `gh release create android-vX.Y.Z "android/dist/openRS_vX.Y.Z.apk#openRS_vX.Y.Z.apk" --title "openRS_ vX.Y.Z — <short description>" --latest --notes "<release notes>"`
- APK must be the **signed** build from `android/dist/`, not debug
- Release notes must summarise every user-visible change
- If firmware changed, create a separate `fw-vX.Y` release and reference it in the app release notes

## 6. GitHub Issues Milestone
- Check the milestone for this release (e.g. `v2.3.0 — Tech Debt + Polish`)
- Verify all issues addressed in this release are closed (commits should auto-close via `fixes #N`)
- Move any unfinished issues to the next milestone

## Quick Verification
Before creating the release, ask:
- [ ] Does `versionName` in `build.gradle.kts` match the CHANGELOG entry?
- [ ] Does the **root** README version badge match?
- [ ] Does the emulator match the app UI?
- [ ] Are any removed widgets also removed from the emulator?
- [ ] Are any formula changes reflected in the emulator and README?
- [ ] Is the APK attached to the GitHub release?
- [ ] Are all addressed issues in the milestone closed?
